
There are many benefits to using functional interfaces in Java 8:

Conciseness: Functional interfaces are a concise way to implement the behavior of a method.
Readability: Functional interfaces can make code more readable by making the code easier to understand.
Maintainability: Functional interfaces can make code more maintainable by making the code easier to change.
Performance: Functional interfaces can improve the performance of code by reducing the amount of code 
that needs to be executed.